{
  "texts": [
    "We trained for 50 epochs, minimizing the original CLIP loss.",
    "The CLIP loss incentivizes the video and text encoders to make the embeddings of paired videos and reports as similar as possible, while making the embeddings of unpaired videos and reports as different as possible (Fig. 1a).",
    "This training objective is, notably, all that is required to make the two models learn to encode their inputs into semantically meaningful vector embeddings.",
    "We warmed up to an initial learning rate of 5 × 10 -5 over the course of the first 2,000 training steps and then cosine decayed to zero over the course of the training run.",
    "We used a batch size of 1,024 and trained on two Nvidia RTX A6000 48 GB GPUs for approximately 2 weeks."
  ]
}